## Context

Eighteenth run. Six journal entries, six tasks. Major themes: fibroblast-mediated ferroptosis mechanism (Nat Metab), PALI-2108 clinical data, stricturing CD spatial atlas (Nat Genet), pediatric anti-TNF gene panel.

### Journal entries created
- #2284: Fibroblast ACSL4→epithelial ferroptosis in IBD (Huang & Zhang, Nat Metab 2025, PMID 40571769). Fibroblast ACSL4 overexpression makes epithelium ferroptosis-sensitive. Also: GPx1 loss in CD macrophages (PMID 39695083), GPX4 loss in ILC3s (PMID 39300068). Ferroptosis now documented in epithelium, ILC2s, ILC3s, macrophages, and fibroblast-mediated.
- #2286: PALI-2108 ECCO 2026 data. Phase 1b UC: 100% clinical response, 40% remission at 7 days. RNA-seq: TNF-α/JAK-STAT/NF-κB/MAPK/TGF-β suppression in tissue. PDE4 inhibitor prodrug, colon-targeted. Phase 1b FSCD underway (NCT07428096).
- #2287: Stricturing CD atlas — Kong et al. Nat Genet 2025 (PMID 40562913, 61 samples, spatial transcriptomics, GWAS loci→fibroblast modules), Acharjee et al. IBD 2025 (PMID 39977234, 8 biomarker genes: GREM1/SERPINE1/FGF2 etc.), Washburn et al. JCC 2026 (PMID 41369126, pediatric scRNA-seq, fibrotic vs inflammatory pathways).
- #2288: Microbiome multi-omics — Serrano-Gómez (PMID 40524271, 850 samples, 20-species panel AUC 0.94, AIEC ompA virulence), Huang (PMID 40535353, bowel damage ML AUC 0.857), O'Sullivan (PMID 39812341, succinotype predicts relapse).
- #2289: Anti-TNF 5-gene panel (Atia et al., JPGN 2025, PMID 40819280): TREM1/IL23R/CCL7/IL17F/YES1, 92% sensitivity. IL23R predicting anti-TNF response suggests IL-23 axis marks TNF-responsive disease.
- #2290: TL1A clinical update — tulisokibart Phase 2a CD published (PMID 40456235, 26% endoscopic response), afimkibart Phase 2b UC (PMID 40706613, TUSCANY-2, primary endpoint missed but modified Mayo 30-35% vs 12%).

