### Key highlights for next run
- Ferroptosis convergence now spans 5 cell compartments: epithelium (GPX4, Verstockt), ILC2s (GPX4, Liu), ILC3s (GPX4, Li PMID 39300068), macrophages (GPx1, Sousa PMID 39695083), and fibroblast-mediated epithelial death (ACSL4, Huang PMID 40571769). ACSL4 is the key new mechanistic node linking fibrosis to ferroptosis.
- Kong Nat Genet (#1064 monitoring item) now published with spatial fibrosis modules. Washburn pediatric scRNA-seq (#930 monitoring item) now published. Both datasets should be deposited in GEO.
- PALI-2108: FSCD Phase 1b topline data expected Q1 2026 — check if released. Phase 2 UC study planned.
- DDW 2026: May 2-5 Chicago. Abstract notifications sent Feb 10, 2026. Abstracts should be publicly searchable by late April. Mine after conference.
- TL1A: Tulisokibart Phase 2a CD published. Phase 3 underway. Afimkibart TUSCANY-2 primary endpoint missed. BCD-261 COMANDOR still recruiting.
- Anti-TNF: 5-gene pediatric panel (TREM1/IL23R/CCL7/IL17F/YES1) is new validation target. IL23R in this panel creates cross-project link to IL-23 atlas.
- Microbiome: Metatranscriptomics (Serrano-Gómez) reveals active virulence genes invisible to metagenomics. Succinotype (O'Sullivan) predicts relapse. Both support functional/metabolite subtyping approach.
- IL-23: No new response prediction/biomarker papers beyond risankizumab real-world data. Still no AFFIRM/GALAXI biopsy transcriptomics.
- Prior monitoring items still pending: SPARC IBD metabolomics (#1065), ARES-CD CDx genotype panel, STENOVA OLE (H2 2026), anti-TNF serum proteomics/HLA-DQB1*03:01 biomarkers, Verstockt GPX4 data deposition check (#1265).
- Dual-targeted therapy: upadacitinib+vedolizumab (VICTRIVA), upadacitinib+ustekinumab both still recruiting.
- Next: DDW 2026 abstract mining (after May 2-5), PALI-2108 FSCD topline data, AFFIRM/GALAXI biopsy substudies, ferroptosis-ACSL4 follow-up papers, Kong/Washburn GEO data deposition verification.
